claim.claim-text:
A nuclear power plant, comprising:
a core (1);
a reactor pressure vessel (2) that houses the core (1);
a dry well (4) that houses the reactor pressure vessel (2);
a wet well (5) whose lower portion houses a suppression pool (6) that is connected to the dry well (4) via a LOCA vent pipe (8), and whose upper portion includes a wet well gas phase (7);
a vacuum breaker (9) that allows gas inside the wet well gas phase (7) to flow back into the dry well (4);
a containment vessel (3) that includes the dry well (4), the LOCA vent pipe (8), the wet well (5), and the vacuum breaker (9);
a cooling water pool (13) that is placed outside the containment vessel (3) and stores cooling water (14);
a heat exchanger (16) that includes an inlet plenum (17), an outlet plenum (18), and a plurality of heat exchanger tubes (19) connecting the inlet plenum (17) and the outlet plenum (18) and being at least partially submerged in the cooling water (14);
a gas supply pipe (20) whose one end is connected to the inlet plenum (17) of the heat exchanger (16), and whose other end is connected to the dry well (4) so that gas in the dry well (4) is led to the heat exchanger (16);
a condensate return pipe (21) whose one end is connected to the outlet plenum (18) of the heat exchanger (16), and whose other end is connected to the containment vessel (3) so that condensate inside the heat exchanger (16) is led to the containment vessel (3); and
a gas vent pipe (22) whose one end is connected to the outlet plenum (18) of the heat exchanger (16), and whose other end is connected to an outside of the wet well (5) so that non-condensable gas inside the heat exchanger (16) is released out of the wet well (5), wherein
the gas vent pipe (22) is not connected to the wet well (5).

The nuclear power plant according to claim 1, further comprising:
a filtered venting vessel (51) that is provided outside the dry well (4) and the wet well (5) and that stores decontamination water (52) that is used to decontaminate radioactive substances;
an inlet pipe (53) whose one end is led to the decontamination water (52), and whose other end is led to outside the filtered venting vessel (51);
a gas vent pipe (22) whose one end is connected to the outlet plenum (18) of the heat exchanger (16), and whose other end is connected to the inlet pipe (53) of the filtered venting vessel (51), so that the non-condensable gas inside the heat exchanger (16) is released into the filtered venting vessel (51) outside the wet well (5); and
an outlet pipe (54) that releases gas inside the filtered venting vessel (51) to an environment, wherein
the gas vent pipe (22) is not connected to the wet well (5).

A passive containment cooling system for a nuclear power plant having a containment vessel (3), a dry well (4) and a wet well (5), comprising:
a cooling water pool (13) that is placed outside the containment vessel (3) and stores cooling water (14);
a heat exchanger (16) that includes an inlet plenum (17), an outlet plenum (18), and a plurality of heat exchanger tubes (19) connecting the inlet plenum (17) and the outlet plenum (18) and being at least partially submerged in the cooling water (14);
a gas supply pipe (20) whose one end is connected to the inlet plenum (17) of the heat exchanger (16), and whose other end is connected to the dry well (4) so that gas in the dry well (4) is led to the heat exchanger (16);
a condensate return pipe (21) whose one end is connected to the outlet plenum (18) of the heat exchanger (16), and whose other end is connected to the containment vessel (3) so that condensate inside the heat exchanger (16) is led to the containment vessel (3);
an outer well (32) that is provided outside the dry well (4) and the wet well (5);
a water seal pool (33) that is provided inside the outer well (32) and in which water is stored; and
a gas vent pipe (22) whose one end is connected to the outlet plenum (18) of the heat exchanger (16), and whose other end is placed so as to be submerged in the water seal pool (33), so that the non-condensable gas inside the heat exchanger (16) is released into the outer well (32) outside the wet well (5), wherein
the gas vent pipe (22) is not connected to the wet well (5).
